---
const comparisonRows = [
  {
    bubble: "Capital rewards exposure to the paradigm",
    mature: "Capital demands proof of durable capture",
  },
  {
    bubble: "Capability and narrative dominate",
    mature: "Cost, governance, execution and margins dominate",
  },
  {
    bubble: "Infrastructure spend reads as confidence",
    mature: "Infrastructure spend gets judged for timing and utilization",
  },
  {
    bubble: "Many plausible companies get funded",
    mature: "Fewer companies survive, but the technology spreads further",
  },
  {
    bubble: "The story is exciting and legible",
    mature: "The power map becomes quieter, more selective and more extractive",
  },
];
---

<figure
  class="not-prose my-10 overflow-hidden rounded-2xl border border-border bg-muted/40"
>
  <div class="grid gap-5 p-5 sm:p-6 lg:grid-cols-[0.92fr_1.08fr]">
    <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border bg-background p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-[0.2em] text-accent uppercase">
        Editorial figure
      </p>
      <h3 class="mt-2 text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">
        The investor loses money. The asset survives.
      </h3>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-foreground/80">
        Bubble capital can disappear while the infrastructure, habits and
        technical direction remain. The crash clears the fantasy layer. It does
        not roll the world back.
      </p>

      <div
        class="mt-5 overflow-hidden rounded-2xl border border-border bg-slate-900"
      >
        <svg
          viewBox="0 0 640 300"
          class="h-auto w-full"
          role="img"
          aria-labelledby="post-crash-figure-title post-crash-figure-desc"
        >
          <title id="post-crash-figure-title">
            A subdued infrastructure scene after the boom
          </title>
          <desc id="post-crash-figure-desc">
            Rows of dark racks, cables and quiet equipment suggest physical
            infrastructure that remains after the first investment story has
            broken.
          </desc>
          <defs>
            <linearGradient
              id="post-crash-bg"
              x1="0%"
              x2="0%"
              y1="0%"
              y2="100%"
            >
              <stop offset="0%" stop-color="#1c2330"></stop>
              <stop offset="100%" stop-color="#11161f"></stop>
            </linearGradient>
            <linearGradient
              id="post-crash-floor"
              x1="0%"
              x2="100%"
              y1="0%"
              y2="0%"
            >
              <stop offset="0%" stop-color="#0f141d"></stop>
              <stop offset="100%" stop-color="#1a2230"></stop>
            </linearGradient>
          </defs>

          <rect width="640" height="300" fill="url(#post-crash-bg)"></rect>
          <rect
            x="0"
            y="210"
            width="640"
            height="90"
            fill="url(#post-crash-floor)"></rect>

          <g opacity="0.95">
            <rect x="62" y="76" width="82" height="134" rx="8" fill="#232c3b"
            ></rect>
            <rect x="170" y="62" width="96" height="148" rx="8" fill="#202938"
            ></rect>
            <rect x="294" y="86" width="76" height="124" rx="8" fill="#263143"
            ></rect>
            <rect x="394" y="68" width="102" height="142" rx="8" fill="#1d2634"
            ></rect>
            <rect x="522" y="94" width="62" height="116" rx="8" fill="#243041"
            ></rect>
          </g>

          <g opacity="0.7">
            <path
              d="M 36 114 C 140 106 172 146 274 136 C 352 128 402 100 470 116 C 536 132 584 132 620 122"
              stroke="#ff8a3d"
              stroke-width="4"
              fill="none"></path>
            <path
              d="M 42 146 C 156 138 198 174 286 166 C 350 160 408 130 480 144 C 536 156 588 154 620 148"
              stroke="#6aaed6"
              stroke-width="3"
              fill="none"
              opacity="0.7"></path>
          </g>

          <g fill="#91a0b8" opacity="0.35">
            <rect x="77" y="94" width="52" height="6" rx="3"></rect>
            <rect x="77" y="112" width="52" height="6" rx="3"></rect>
            <rect x="185" y="86" width="66" height="6" rx="3"></rect>
            <rect x="185" y="106" width="66" height="6" rx="3"></rect>
            <rect x="309" y="104" width="46" height="6" rx="3"></rect>
            <rect x="409" y="92" width="72" height="6" rx="3"></rect>
            <rect x="409" y="112" width="72" height="6" rx="3"></rect>
            <rect x="535" y="112" width="36" height="6" rx="3"></rect>
          </g>

          <rect
            x="28"
            y="28"
            width="220"
            height="52"
            rx="12"
            fill="#101621"
            stroke="#344054"></rect>
          <text
            x="48"
            y="48"
            fill="#ffb37d"
            font-size="12"
            font-family="ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, monospace"
            letter-spacing="2"
          >
            AFTER THE BOOM
          </text>
          <text
            x="48"
            y="68"
            fill="#eef2f8"
            font-size="18"
            font-family="ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, monospace"
          >
            Infrastructure outlives the story
          </text>
        </svg>
      </div>

      <div
        class="mt-4 rounded-2xl border border-border bg-muted/35 p-4 text-sm leading-6 text-foreground/75"
      >
        This is the chapter's core emotional shift: the capital structure can
        fail even when the technical substrate remains useful.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border bg-background p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-[0.2em] text-accent uppercase">
        Bubble phase versus mature phase
      </p>
      <div
        class="mt-4 grid grid-cols-[1fr_1fr] gap-3 text-xs font-semibold tracking-[0.18em] text-foreground/60 uppercase"
      >
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-muted/40 px-3 py-2">
          Bubble phase
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-muted/40 px-3 py-2">
          Mature phase after the break
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-3 space-y-3">
        {
          comparisonRows.map(row => (
            <div class="grid gap-3 sm:grid-cols-2">
              <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border bg-muted/35 p-4 text-sm leading-6 text-foreground/75">
                {row.bubble}
              </div>
              <div class="rounded-2xl border border-accent/20 bg-accent/5 p-4 text-sm leading-6 text-foreground/80">
                {row.mature}
              </div>
            </div>
          ))
        }
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <figcaption
    class="border-t border-border/70 px-5 py-4 text-sm leading-6 text-foreground/70 sm:px-6"
  >
    The crash does not end the paradigm. It forces the technology into a more
    selective, more disciplined and often more extractive mature form.
  </figcaption>
</figure>
